§3§nPrinting Enchanted Books

§21.§r Place §7Print Press Chase§r in top slot of Typesetting Table and your enchanted book in left slot.

§22§..§r Shift right-click on your enchanted book, this will make §dEnchanted Plate§r and consume §a40 levels§r.

§23§..§r Take enchanted plate and place it in Printing Press (aim at top center of the block).

§24.§r Right-click with an §8Ink Sac§r (aim above the enchanted plate).

§25.§r Right-click normal Book in lower left corner.

§3§3§3Note:§r§r§r Make sure to print one book at the time, because plate has only §4§4§43 uses§r§r§r, which can be repaired with §3§3§3Magic Mending Solution§r§r§r.

§3§nHow to Repairing Items

§21.§r Right-click with Bucket of Lava on the Filtration System.

§22.§r Craft Magic Mending Compound.

§23.§r Right-click with a Metal Tub on Filtration System to make Magic Mending Solution, this will consume mending compound.

§24.§r Right-click with the item that you need to repair on Mending Table, this will consume mending solution.

§25.§r Done.

Works on any item that has durability.

§3§nApoco Minigame§r

Use the §3Apoco Stone§r on the Exoid Station to summon First Exoid. Once the first Exoid is killed, a new Exoid will spawn within a 45 block radius of the old one. The player will then have to go and find this Exoid. Killing this second Exoid will spawn in a third one in a 45 block radius of itself, and the process repeats. If the player takes too long to find and kill an Exoid, the Exoid will explode, leaving no reward. The fifth and final Exoid will drop the §2Doom Stone §rand Vox Realmstone.

§2Found in Strange Shrine, which generates randomly in Shyrelands rooms.§r
